mental wellbeing cut across age and class differences and have profound impacts on the material conditions of women's lives throughout the life course. This is in turn a driver of inequality that is often under-recognised in mainstream policy. Based on feminist and ethnographically informed research with over five hundred women Gendering women provides a critical link between gender theory and the lived realities of women's daily lives and will appeal to students and academics in sociology and social sciences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh1 aHoldsworth, Julia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311119634340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847426789zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847426789/original  a978-3-11-119634-3 Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA